    • Method Detail

      • extractClassNameFromFile

        public static String extractClassNameFromFile(File parentDirectory,
                                              File classFile)
                                       throws IOException
        Remove parent directory from file name and replace directory separator with dots.
        • parentDirectory: /tmp/my/parent/src/
        • classFile: /tmp/my/parent/src/foo/bar/MyApp.class
        returns: foo.bar.MyApp
        Parameters:
        parentDirectory - to remove from classFile and maybe null.
        classFile - to extract the name from. Maybe null
        Returns:
        class name extracted from file name or null
        Throws:
        IOException - by file operations

      • iterateClassnames

        public static Iterator<String> iterateClassnames(File parentDirectory,
                                                 File... classFiles)
        Iterate over the class files and remove the parent directory from file name and replace directory separator with dots.
        Parameters:
        parentDirectory - to remove from classFile and maybe null.
        classFiles - array to extract the names from. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        iterator of full qualified class names based on passed classFiles
        See Also:
        iterateClassnames(File, Iterator)

      • iterateClassnames

        public static Iterator<String> iterateClassnames(File parentDirectory,
                                                 Iterator<File> classFileIterator)
        Wrapping the iterator (as reference) of class file names and extract full qualified class name on Iterator.next().

        It is possible that Iterator.hasNext() returns true and Iterator.next() returns null.

        Parameters:
        parentDirectory - to remove from classFile and maybe null.
        classFileIterator - to extract the names from. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        iterator of full qualified class names based on passed classFiles or null
        See Also:
        extractClassNameFromFile(File, File)
